  <main class="container doc">
    <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p class="muted"><strong>Effective:</strong> 24 August 2025 · <strong>Last Updated:</strong> 24 August 2025</p>

    <p>Social Stuff (“we,” “our,” “us”) values your privacy and is committed to protecting your personal information. This policy explains what we collect, how we use it, and your rights when using the Social Stuff mobile and web applications (the “App”). By using the App, you agree to this policy.</p>

    <h2>1. Information We Collect</h2>
    <h3>a) Information You Provide</h3>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Account Data:</strong> name, email, profile photo, chosen pronouns, social log-in (Google, Facebook, Microsoft, etc.).</li>
      <li><strong>Profile Data:</strong> communities joined, interests, bio, preferences.</li>
      <li><strong>Event Data:</strong> events you create, RSVP to, attend, or host.</li>
      <li><strong>Communications:</strong> messages in-app, feedback, support requests.</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>c) Third-Party Sources</h3>
    <p>We may receive data from identity providers (e.g., Google, Facebook, Microsoft) when you sign in, subject to their privacy policies.</p>

    <h2>2. How We Use Your Information</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Provide, personalise, and improve the App.</li>
      <li>Facilitate event discovery, RSVPs, and community participation.</li>
      <li>Enable event creation and hosting tools.</li>
      <li>Provide AR view to help users locate hosts and groups.</li>
      <li>Ensure safety, enforce our Code of Conduct, and prevent abuse.</li>
      <li>Communicate with you (updates, support, announcements).</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>3. Sharing of Information</h2>
    <p>We do not sell your personal data. We may share:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>With other users:</strong> your profile name, photo, and RSVP status when you join events or communities.</li>
      <li><strong>With hosts:</strong> event hosts see RSVPs to their events.</li>
      <li><strong>With service providers:</strong> hosting, analytics, cloud storage, payments (if applicable).</li>
      <li><strong>Legal obligations:</strong> where required by law, court order, or to protect rights/safety.</li>
      <li><strong>Business transfers:</strong> in a merger, acquisition, or sale of assets.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>4. Data Retention</h2>
    <p>We retain personal data while your account is active or as needed to provide the App and meet legal obligations. You may request deletion of your account and associated data.</p>

    <h2>5. Security</h2>
    <p>We use appropriate technical and organisational measures to protect information; however, no system is 100% secure.</p>

    <h2>6. Your Rights</h2>
    <p>Depending on your location, you may have rights to access, correct, delete, restrict/ object to processing, withdraw consent (e.g., location), and data portability. Contact: <a href="mailto:privacy@socialstuff.app">privacy@socialstuff.app</a>.</p>

    <h2>7. Children’s Privacy</h2>
    <p>The App is for users aged 18+ only. We do not knowingly collect data from children. If we learn we have, we will delete it.</p>

    <h2>8. International Transfers</h2>
    <p>Your data may be processed outside your country. We take steps to ensure appropriate safeguards are in place.</p>

    <h2>9. Third-Party Links</h2>
    <p>Events or communities may include links to third-party sites/services. We are not responsible for their privacy practices.</p>

    <h2>10. Changes</h2>
    <p>We may update this policy. Significant changes will be notified in-app or by email. Please review periodically.</p>


